OL,3,CCan sleeper trains transform travel in
OL,4,CEurope?
OL,6,F"Sleeper trains are the most difficult
OL,7,Fto make work commercially," says Mark
OL,8,FSmith, who runs the travel website The
OL,9,FMan in Seat 61 and is also onboard
OL,10,Ftonight's inaugural journey.
OL,12,F"You've got 20 or 30 people in beds,
OL,13,Fwhereas in the same coach if it had
OL,14,Fseats and on a daytime train, you
OL,15,Fcould get 70 people in."
OL,17,FDemand has always been there, he says,
OL,18,Fbut operators savvy enough to balance
OL,19,Fthe books have not.
